reviews.review: Kelly is so kind and shows that she wants her students to succeed. She is very kind and is easy to talk to if you have any issues or questions about anything. I am happy to have her as my teacher for 2 year in scholars and I know I can count on her even after I graduate the program.
Kelly thinks of you as a student first and always wants you to succeed academically. Overall a nice professor and pretty laid back.

She really cares about her students and is always willing to help. The class itself is very easy and isn't very content heavy, but does teach you some important concepts. Grade consists of mostly exit tickets.
Kelly cares so deeply about all her students and is such a joy to learn from

Kelly is very nice and relatable and you can tell she really cares about her students. The class is easy and kind of pointless where you "learn" like how to find the counseling center and about identities and such. Most of the grade is based on a website you build called an e portfolio but its basically busy work.
